# Cloudflare header rules. GitHub Pages hardcoded Cache-Control: max-age=600 on everything
# with no way to override it -- that's the original cause of scores taking up to 10-20
# minutes to show up after a refresh. `no-cache` still allows cheap ETag revalidation; it
# just stops the browser/CDN from blindly trusting a stale copy.
#
# Catch-all, not scoped to /*.html -- Workers Static Assets redirects "/foo.html" requests
# to the extensionless "/foo", and that's the path that actually serves the content, so a
# pattern scoped to ".html" silently misses it and falls through to Cloudflare's default
# edge caching (confirmed: this caused tournament_app.html itself to serve stale content
# after a deploy, even though the redirect response was correctly no-cache).
/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache
